verbose_text: This decrease in O acetylated sialic acids is associated with a concomitant increase in expression of the sialylated antigens, sialyl Tn, sialyl Lewis (a), and sialyl Lewis (x), which are considered to be adverse prognostic indicators.
evidence: expression of the sialylated antigens, sialyl Tn, sialyl Lewis (a), and sialyl Lewis (x)
